  "title": "Baseball Pitcher",
  "difficulty": "Easy",
  "question_text": "<div class=\"paragraph\">A baseball player claims he throws <span class=\"tex2jax_process\">$90\\%$</span> strikes when he's pitching. His AP Statistics attends the next game he pitches, and records the number of strikes. The baseball player threw <span class=\"tex2jax_process\">$80\\%$</span> strikes during the game the teacher attended. </div><div class=\"paragraph\">The teacher decides to run a simulation with a random number generator where the proportion of strikes is known to be <span class=\"tex2jax_process\">$0.9$</span>. What question is the teacher most likely trying to answer?</div>",
  "image_files": [],
  "choices": [
    {
      "letter": "A",
      "text": "How many strikes the player will throw in his next game?"
    },
    {
      "letter": "B",
      "text": "What is the shape of the distribution of proportion of strikes?"
    },
    {
      "letter": "C",
      "text": "What is the expected number of strikes the player will throw?"
    },
    {
      "letter": "D",
      "text": "How likely is it that a true\n90\n%\nstrike thrower will only throw\n80\n%\nstrikes?"
    },
    {
      "letter": "E",
      "text": "What are the odds the player throws\n80\n%\nstrikes in the next game?"
    }
  ],
  "correct_answer": "<strong>Choice 'D'</strong> is the correct answer. ",
  "solution": "Since the teacher was told the proportion of strikes the student should be throwing was <span class=\"tex2jax_process\"><span class=\"MathJax_Preview\" style=\"color: inherit;\"></span><span id=\"MathJax-Element-17018-Frame\" class=\"mjx-chtml MathJax_CHTML\" tabindex=\"0\" data-mathml=\"<math xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&quot;><mn>90</mn><mi mathvariant=&quot;normal&quot;>&amp;#x0025;</mi></math>\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"font-size: 114%; position: relative;\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91338\" class=\"mjx-math\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91339\" class=\"mjx-mrow\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91340\" class=\"mjx-mn\"><span class=\"mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R\" style=\"padding-top: 0.387em; padding-bottom: 0.387em;\">90</span></span><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91341\" class=\"mjx-mi\"><span class=\"mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R\" style=\"padding-top: 0.441em; padding-bottom: 0.387em;\">%</span></span></span></span><span class=\"MJX_Assistive_MathML\" role=\"presentation\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>90</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">%</mi></math></span></span><script type=\"math/tex\" id=\"MathJax-Element-17018\">90\\%</script></span>, the teacher should expect the student to be around <span class=\"tex2jax_process\"><span class=\"MathJax_Preview\" style=\"color: inherit;\"></span><span id=\"MathJax-Element-17019-Frame\" class=\"mjx-chtml MathJax_CHTML\" tabindex=\"0\" data-mathml=\"<math xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&quot;><mn>90</mn><mi mathvariant=&quot;normal&quot;>&amp;#x0025;</mi></math>\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"font-size: 114%; position: relative;\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91342\" class=\"mjx-math\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91343\" class=\"mjx-mrow\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91344\" class=\"mjx-mn\"><span class=\"mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R\" style=\"padding-top: 0.387em; padding-bottom: 0.387em;\">90</span></span><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91345\" class=\"mjx-mi\"><span class=\"mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R\" style=\"padding-top: 0.441em; padding-bottom: 0.387em;\">%</span></span></span></span><span class=\"MJX_Assistive_MathML\" role=\"presentation\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>90</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">%</mi></math></span></span><script type=\"math/tex\" id=\"MathJax-Element-17019\">90\\%</script></span>. When the teacher observed the student, the student only threw <span class=\"tex2jax_process\"><span class=\"MathJax_Preview\" style=\"color: inherit;\"></span><span id=\"MathJax-Element-17020-Frame\" class=\"mjx-chtml MathJax_CHTML\" tabindex=\"0\" data-mathml=\"<math xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&quot;><mn>80</mn><mi mathvariant=&quot;normal&quot;>&amp;#x0025;</mi></math>\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"font-size: 114%; position: relative;\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91346\" class=\"mjx-math\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91347\" class=\"mjx-mrow\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91348\" class=\"mjx-mn\"><span class=\"mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R\" style=\"padding-top: 0.387em; padding-bottom: 0.387em;\">80</span></span><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91349\" class=\"mjx-mi\"><span class=\"mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R\" style=\"padding-top: 0.441em; padding-bottom: 0.387em;\">%</span></span></span></span><span class=\"MJX_Assistive_MathML\" role=\"presentation\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>80</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">%</mi></math></span></span><script type=\"math/tex\" id=\"MathJax-Element-17020\">80\\%</script></span> strikes.  The teacher has to ask, \"Is this close enough to <span class=\"tex2jax_process\"><span class=\"MathJax_Preview\" style=\"color: inherit;\"></span><span id=\"MathJax-Element-17021-Frame\" class=\"mjx-chtml MathJax_CHTML\" tabindex=\"0\" data-mathml=\"<math xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&quot;><mn>90</mn><mi mathvariant=&quot;normal&quot;>&amp;#x0025;</mi></math>\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"font-size: 114%; position: relative;\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91350\" class=\"mjx-math\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91351\" class=\"mjx-mrow\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91352\" class=\"mjx-mn\"><span class=\"mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R\" style=\"padding-top: 0.387em; padding-bottom: 0.387em;\">90</span></span><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91353\" class=\"mjx-mi\"><span class=\"mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R\" style=\"padding-top: 0.441em; padding-bottom: 0.387em;\">%</span></span></span></span><span class=\"MJX_Assistive_MathML\" role=\"presentation\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>90</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">%</mi></math></span></span><script type=\"math/tex\" id=\"MathJax-Element-17021\">90\\%</script></span>, or do I have evidence the student is not a <span class=\"tex2jax_process\"><span class=\"MathJax_Preview\" style=\"color: inherit;\"></span><span id=\"MathJax-Element-17022-Frame\" class=\"mjx-chtml MathJax_CHTML\" tabindex=\"0\" data-mathml=\"<math xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&quot;><mn>90</mn><mi mathvariant=&quot;normal&quot;>&amp;#x0025;</mi></math>\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"font-size: 114%; position: relative;\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91354\" class=\"mjx-math\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91355\" class=\"mjx-mrow\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91356\" class=\"mjx-mn\"><span class=\"mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R\" style=\"padding-top: 0.387em; padding-bottom: 0.387em;\">90</span></span><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91357\" class=\"mjx-mi\"><span class=\"mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R\" style=\"padding-top: 0.441em; padding-bottom: 0.387em;\">%</span></span></span></span><span class=\"MJX_Assistive_MathML\" role=\"presentation\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>90</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">%</mi></math></span></span><script type=\"math/tex\" id=\"MathJax-Element-17022\">90\\%</script></span> strike-thrower?\"\n\nTherefore, by doing a simulation where the known proportion of strikes thrown is <span class=\"tex2jax_process\"><span class=\"MathJax_Preview\" style=\"color: inherit;\"></span><span id=\"MathJax-Element-17023-Frame\" class=\"mjx-chtml MathJax_CHTML\" tabindex=\"0\" data-mathml=\"<math xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&quot;><mn>90</mn><mi mathvariant=&quot;normal&quot;>&amp;#x0025;</mi></math>\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"font-size: 114%; position: relative;\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91358\" class=\"mjx-math\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91359\" class=\"mjx-mrow\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91360\" class=\"mjx-mn\"><span class=\"mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R\" style=\"padding-top: 0.387em; padding-bottom: 0.387em;\">90</span></span><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91361\" class=\"mjx-mi\"><span class=\"mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R\" style=\"padding-top: 0.441em; padding-bottom: 0.387em;\">%</span></span></span></span><span class=\"MJX_Assistive_MathML\" role=\"presentation\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>90</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">%</mi></math></span></span><script type=\"math/tex\" id=\"MathJax-Element-17023\">90\\%</script></span>, the teacher is seeing if <span class=\"tex2jax_process\"><span class=\"MathJax_Preview\" style=\"color: inherit;\"></span><span id=\"MathJax-Element-17024-Frame\" class=\"mjx-chtml MathJax_CHTML\" tabindex=\"0\" data-mathml=\"<math xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&quot;><mn>80</mn><mi mathvariant=&quot;normal&quot;>&amp;#x0025;</mi></math>\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"font-size: 114%; position: relative;\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91362\" class=\"mjx-math\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91363\" class=\"mjx-mrow\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91364\" class=\"mjx-mn\"><span class=\"mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R\" style=\"padding-top: 0.387em; padding-bottom: 0.387em;\">80</span></span><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91365\" class=\"mjx-mi\"><span class=\"mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R\" style=\"padding-top: 0.441em; padding-bottom: 0.387em;\">%</span></span></span></span><span class=\"MJX_Assistive_MathML\" role=\"presentation\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>80</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">%</mi></math></span></span><script type=\"math/tex\" id=\"MathJax-Element-17024\">80\\%</script></span> happens enough by chance to say the player could actually be a <span class=\"tex2jax_process\"><span class=\"MathJax_Preview\" style=\"color: inherit;\"></span><span id=\"MathJax-Element-17025-Frame\" class=\"mjx-chtml MathJax_CHTML\" tabindex=\"0\" data-mathml=\"<math xmlns=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML&quot;><mn>90</mn><mi mathvariant=&quot;normal&quot;>&amp;#x0025;</mi></math>\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"font-size: 114%; position: relative;\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91366\" class=\"mjx-math\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91367\" class=\"mjx-mrow\"><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91368\" class=\"mjx-mn\"><span class=\"mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R\" style=\"padding-top: 0.387em; padding-bottom: 0.387em;\">90</span></span><span id=\"MJXc-Node-91369\" class=\"mjx-mi\"><span class=\"mjx-char MJXc-TeX-main-R\" style=\"padding-top: 0.441em; padding-bottom: 0.387em;\">%</span></span></span></span><span class=\"MJX_Assistive_MathML\" role=\"presentation\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>90</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">%</mi></math></span></span><script type=\"math/tex\" id=\"MathJax-Element-17025\">90\\%</script></span> strike-thrower and this game just happened by chance.  \n\n<strong>Choice 'D'</strong> is correct. ",
  "distractor_explanations": {
    "A": "<strong>Choice 'A'</strong> is incorrect. The simulation will not show how many strikes the player will throw in the next game, it is not a predictive tool. ",
    "B": "<strong>Choice 'B'</strong> is incorrect. The shape of the distribution is unknown until we have a certain number of trials performed. ",
    "C": "<strong>Choice 'C'</strong> is incorrect. Without knowing the true probability of throwing a strike, we cannot find the expected number of strikes thrown. ",
    "E": "<strong>Choice 'E'</strong> is incorrect. Again the simulation is not a predictive tool. Therefore, it will not tell us the proportion of strikes thrown in the next game."
